  "prompt": "Which is the best website for booking cheap air tickets?",
  "response": "There's no single \"best\" website for booking cheap air tickets, as prices fluctuate constantly and depend on various factors like:\n\n*   **Destination:** Certain websites may specialize in specific regions.\n*   **Travel Dates:** Prices vary significantly based on the time of year and day of the week.\n*   **Flexibility:** If you're flexible with your dates and destinations, you can find better deals.\n*   **Airline:** Some airlines don't appear on all booking sites.\n\nHowever, here's a list of popular and generally reliable websites that are often recommended for finding cheap air tickets, along with their strengths:\n\n**General Search Engines (Aggregate Results from Multiple Sources):**\n\n*   **Google Flights:** (flights.google.com)  **Strengths:** Powerful search capabilities, price tracking, explore map to find cheap destinations, shows calendar of prices for flexibility.  **Weaknesses:** Doesn't always include all smaller airlines.\n*   **Kayak:** (kayak.com)  **Strengths:** Good for comparing prices, \"Explore\" feature, price alerts.\n*   **Skyscanner:** (skyscanner.com)  **Strengths:**  Extremely flexible search options (e.g., \"Everywhere\" destination, \"Whole Month\" dates), price alerts.\n*   **Momondo:** (momondo.com)  **Strengths:**  Often finds slightly different results than other aggregators.\n*   **Kiwi.com:** (kiwi.com) **Strengths:** Specializes in connecting flights from different airlines that aren't typically booked together, often resulting in lower prices.  **Weaknesses:**  Can be risky if flights are delayed or canceled, as they may not have the same guarantees as booking directly with an airline. Read their policies carefully.\n\n**Direct Airline Websites:**\n\n*   **Southwest Airlines:** (southwest.com)  **Strengths:**  Often good for domestic US flights, no change fees (but fare differences may apply), two free checked bags. **Weaknesses:**  Not found on most aggregator sites; must check directly.\n*   **Major Airlines (e.g., United, American, Delta, etc.):**  **Strengths:**  Booking directly gives you more control over your booking and better support in case of issues.  **Weaknesses:**  May not always be the cheapest.\n\n**Other Tips for Finding Cheap Flights:**\n\n*   **Be Flexible:** The more flexible you are with your travel dates and destination, the better your chances of finding a good deal. Consider flying on weekdays or during off-peak seasons.\n*   **Set Price Alerts:** Use the price tracking features on Google Flights, Kayak, or Skyscanner to get notified when prices drop.\n*   **Consider Budget Airlines:**  Airlines like Ryanair, EasyJet, Spirit, Frontier, and Allegiant often have very low base fares, but be aware of extra fees for baggage, seat selection, and other services.\n*   **Clear Your Cookies and Browser History:**  Some websites may track your searches and increase prices accordingly.\n*   **Check Alternate Airports:**  Flying into or out of a smaller, less busy airport can sometimes save you money.\n*   **Book in Advance (But Not Too Far in Advance):**  The \"sweet spot\" for booking domestic flights is often 1-3 months in advance.  For international flights, 2-8 months in advance is often recommended.\n*   **Consider Package Deals:** Sometimes booking a flight and hotel together can save you money.\n\n**How to Use the Websites Effectively:**\n\n1.  **Start with a general search engine (Google Flights, Kayak, Skyscanner) to get an overview of available flights and prices.**\n2.  **If you find a good deal on an aggregator site, always double-check the price on the airline's website before booking.**  Sometimes booking directly with the airline is cheaper, and it usually provides better customer service if something goes wrong.\n3.  **If you're flying Southwest, check their website directly.**\n4.  **Consider using Kiwi.com if you're comfortable with the potential risks.**\n\n**In conclusion, the \"best\" website is the one that finds you the cheapest flight for your specific needs and travel dates. Use a combination of the above resources and tips to find the best deal.**\n",
